I am developing a feature for our mobile application that allows users to book guided tours for popular tourist destinations. I am facing a problem with the alignment of tour details within the booking page on mobile devices. When a user selects a tour, the details of that tour should be displayed at the top of the screen. However, I am experiencing an issue where the tour details are displayed a few pixels below the top of the screen on various mobile devices. I am using the following code to display the tour details:

```javascript
var selectedTour = getSelectedTour();
var tourDetails = document.getElementById('tour-details');
tourDetails.innerHTML = getTourDetails(selectedTour);
tourDetails.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'start' });
```

The tour details are displayed correctly but a few pixels below the top of the screen on various mobile devices. How can I ensure that the tour details are displayed at the exact top of the screen on different mobile devices, considering the varying screen sizes and operating systems?
